What is sort of that as a clean number and happy to take it offline, but I’m actually just trying to back out how well TRG did this quarter prior – compared to prior quarters given the…
 The $18 million was primarily from the excess investment of our – for the Tobin purchase. Well, I think what you’re seeing is the fact that we have some big account leasing that we are not rushing to do, but doing it in a thoughtful manner, because we – these are really good properties and really important for the retailer and we’re taking our time to get that done. But just – because I think what I’m trying to get at is guidance implying that are releasing spreads could be negative or – like I’m just trying to figure out what the pullback years of expense is, because I get the variability portion. And like I mentioned in the call, I mean our terminations were at the lowest level they’ve been in a long, long time and our deal committee, I think we’ve had a – we have a really good leasing group.
